
process: 
--> A process is a program in execution
--> it is simply a running instance of a program
--> A process is simply a program that is currently running


-types of processes:
1. foreground process:
--> A foreground process runs in the terminal and uses the terminal until it finishes.
--> you can not use the terminal for another command while it is running.
eg: gzip, find, mkdir

2. background process:
--> these processes runs in a background without blocking your terminal.
--> the terminal is free
--> you can continue typing other commands

3. daemon process:
--> A daemon process is a special background process that starts automatically
and keeps running to provide service.
eg: initd, sshd

-Runnning a proccess in background
--> use the & symbol to start a process in the background
eg:
command &
sleep 100&
sleep 60&
